SEC. 13.

Implementing Rules and Regulations. -

The DOTr, in consultation with the DTI, DOH, Department of the Interior and Local Government (DILG), Philippine National Police-Highway Patrol Group (PNP-HPG), Metro Manila Development Authority (MMDA), Council for the Welfare of Children (CWC) and other concerned agencies and stakeholders, shall promulgate the IRR on child restraint systems within six (6) months from the effectivity of this Act.

The IRR shall cover among others the following:

(a) Motor vehicles covered under this Act;

(b) Standards and kinds of child restraint systems based on UN Regulations 44 and 129;

(c) Compatibility of child restraint systems to motor vehicles available in the market;

(d) Proper installation and positioning of the child restraint system in the vehicle;

(e) Certification training program referred to in Section 8 of this Act for law enforcers, products inspectors, employees and agents of manufacturers, distributors, sellers and importers;

(f) Regulation of the manufacture, importation, and distribution of child restraint system;

(f) Regulation of the manufacture, importation, and distribution of child restraint system;

(g) Authorities responsible for the monitoring and evaluation of the implementation and compliance to the provisions of this Act; and

(h) Phases of implementation.
